   INDONESIA-DEMOCRACY (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ Everything has
changed in Indonesia since its strongman, Suharto, was pushed from
office just two years ago. The clamor of democracy is everywhere,
along with the violence and instability that accompany a time of
unfettered transformation. And nothing has changed. Indonesia is
still focused on the ideas, the directives _ even the whims _ of
one man, its new president, Abdurrahman Wahid. By Seth Mydans.
1,300 words.
