participation, disrupting insurance coverage for hundreds of
thousands of elderly people, according to federal officials,
independent experts and managed care executives. Cigna Corp. said
Friday that it would end coverage for 104,000 Medicare
beneficiaries in 11 states: New York, New Jersey, Connecticut,
California, Delaware, Florida, Georgia, Maryland, Tennessee, Texas
and Virginia. By Robert Pear. 1,600 words.
