   CANADA-AIRLINES (Calgary, Alberta) _ After Air Canada's
acquisition of Canadian Airlines this spring, Canadians are waking
up to an airline market more reliant on a single carrier than in
any other major Western nation. Air Canada has 82 percent of the
market _ far above the 60 percent held by Lufthansa in Germany. But
with passengers and lawmakers complaining that the merger has
created a monopoly, the government is encouraging discount
airlines. And there are, increasingly, alternatives. By James
Brooke.
