<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-03 01:35 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3508 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s BC-BKN-LAKERS-BLAZERS-NY     06-03 0738
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-BLAZERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BLAZERS' PLAY FORCES THE LAKERS TO GAME 7
</HEADLINE>
  By TOM SPOUSTA   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. _ They wore determined looks and shook their
heads from side to side, gesturing to the Los Angeles Lakers
throughout Game 6 that the Western Conference finals would not end
in their house.
</P>
<P>
   Friday night the Portland Trail Blazers protected the Rose
Garden like pit bulls, stopping the Lakers at every key moment for
a 103-93 victory to tie the series at 3-3 and force Game 7 on
Sunday in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   After falling behind by 3-1, the Trail Blazers are in position
to become only the seventh team in NBA history to win a best-of-7
series after falling behind by 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Smith, the 31-year-old guard, fired daggers into the
Lakers' hearts throughout the game and finished with 26 points.
Rasheed Wallace added 18 and Damon Stoudamire 14. Scottie Pippen,
quiet through three quarters, contributed nine points and several
clutch defensive plays.
</P>
<P>
   Kobe Bryant had 33 points and Shaquille O'Neal had 17, his
lowest total against Portland this season, and 11 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our guys came out with a passion and the intensity that had
been lacking in previous games,'' Portland coach Mike Dunleavy
said. ``There's no fear factor for us going down there. Everybody
wanted a Game 7. Now we got one.''
</P>
<P>
   Bonzi Wells energized an already raucous home crowd with 20
points in 19 minutes. Wells, who played only six minutes in three
quarters, hit back-to-back baskets to give the Trail Blazers a
79-68 lead with 9 minutes 11 seconds to play. Moments later, Brian
Grant hit two free throws to put Portland ahead by 13 and force the
Lakers to scramble.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike Games 3 and 4, when the Trail Blazers blew double-digit
leads, they held steady in the third quarter Friday night. The
Lakers could chip only two points off Portland's lead and trailed
by 71-63. A dunk and a jump shot by Wallace and two free throws
each from Pippen and Smith held off a Los Angeles surge, before
Bryant drilled a 3-pointer with 1.3 seconds left in the quarter to
move the Lakers within eight points.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers cut their 10-point halftime deficit to 49-44 with a
3-point play by Ron Harper and a 3-point shot from Glen Rice. The
Trail Blazers quickly countered, though, with a 10-5 run for some
breathing space at 58-49 midway through the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The Trail Blazers' 49-39 halftime lead was earned without any
offense from Pippen, who took only one shot, a 3-pointer in the
second quarter. Pippen's presence was felt with three rebounds and
two assists, but mostly he left the heavy lifting to Smith,
Stoudamire and Wallace.
</P>
<P>
   Smith and Stoudamire scored 12 points each and Wallace added 11
as the Trail Blazers twice built 15-point leads early in the second
quarter. Smith was 6 of 9 from the field and Stoudamire, easily
surpassing his 8.8-point average for the series, hit 6 of 10
field-goal attempts.
</P>
<P>
   Wallace came alive late in the second quarter with seven points.
His short jump shot and dunk in the final 1:30 held off a Lakers'
rally that had twice pulled them within eight points.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant, nursing a sprained foot suffered early in Game 5, led
the Lakers in the first half with 14 points.
</P>
<P>
   As for most of the series, O'Neal was ominously quiet in the
first half. With the Trail Blazers sticking to him like lint, he
made 4 of 8 field-goal attempts for eight points and grabbed five
rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if we got in their heads,'' Stoudamire had said
before the tip-off. ``But we gave them something to think about. I
definitely don't think they thought they were coming back to
Portland.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of people had buried us. Probably the only people in the
country who thought we were going to win that last game was us.''
</P>
<P>
   Portland's mission was apparent from the start. Once again, the
Trail Blazers flung themselves at the Lakers from all angles and
set a blistering pace. Smith and Stoudamire were especially hot,
carrying the Trail Blazers to a 26-15 lead through one quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant was in the starting lineup despite his sprained foot,
although concern about his injury caused the Lakers to make a
defensive adjustment.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant had guarded Pippen for most of the series, but was
switched to Stoudamire. Rice was assigned to Pippen, a matchup that
the Trail Blazers did not need to exploit after they blitzed the
Lakers early.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
