<P>
   ENIGMA _ WASHINGTON _ British newspapers are indignant about the
American movie ``U-571,'' which depicts the British World War II
submarine crew that captured a critical German code machine known
as Enigma as American ``heroes.'' ``Film Steals Hero's Glory,''
said the Sunday Mercury in a typical comment Bemused and irked by
the trans-Atlantic tempest are members of the Polish-American
community, because Poles _ not Britons and not Americans _ actually
captured the super-secret machine. (Weglarczyk and Nesmith, Cox
News Service).
</P>
