 &HT;    BAD HURRICANE YEAR PREDICTED
 &HT;    Compiled by Staff
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Leading hurricane forecasters are predicting more hurricane
activity than the average for the last half of the century.
</P>
<P>
   Forecast Average for 2000 (1950-1990)
</P>
<P>
   Named storms 119.3
</P>
<P>
   Hurricanes 75.8
</P>
<P>
   Hurricane days 25 23.7
</P>
<P>
   Intense hurricanes 32.2
</P>
<P>
   The probability of one or more major hurricanes (minimum wind
speed 115 mph) also is expected to be higher than average this
year.
</P>
<P>
   2000 Average for forecast last century
</P>
<P>
   Eastern Seaboard 39% 31%(including Florida Peninsula)
</P>
<P>
   Gulf Coast 34% 31%(from Florida Panhandle to Brownsville, Texas)
</P>
