<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for SUNDAY, JUNE 4. If you have
any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
WAGE _ Starting pay for most entry-level positions in Arizona, such
as customer service representatives, nurses assistants and office
clerks, is $10 an hour, according to Arizona companies. That's well
above the national minimum wage of $5.15 an hour, evenwell above
the higher minimum wage of $6.15 an hour being proposed by
President Clinton. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TRASH _ In this booming economy, we are buying and replacing and
throwing away like never before. Nationally, people bought 40
percent more stuff _ cars, armchairs, toasters and computers _ last
year than four years ago, the U.S. Department of Commerce says. And
in the Phoenix metro area, where there are few basements and fewer
attics, we must confront our stuff. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WASTE-MINING _ Because of hard-rock mine waste, Arizona has had
more toxic releases than any state but Nevada. The numbers,
recently released by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency,
suggest that the decades of prosperity generated by hardrock mining
in Arizona have come at a price. How big a price is in dispute
between industry and environmentalists. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) _ A young mother, much like the young
mother of ElianGonzalez, gave up her life last week during a brave
but foolish attempt to bring her child into this country, and from
the politicians we hear nothing. They speak with misty affection
about how Elian's mother sacrificed her life to provide a better
future for her child. It's exactly what this other mother did, and
still they say nothing. Because she didn't come from Cuba. She came
from Mexico. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NEW&AMP;NOTABLE (undated) _ Anne Stephenson's capsule reviews of new
books. By ANNE STEPHENSON. Story will move in the ``E'' and ``L''
categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WEB&AMP;MAGS (undated) _ Bill Muller's reviews of a website and some
current magazines. By BILL MULLER. Story will move in the ``E'' and
``L'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-GOODY-SEX (Undated) - There is TV for chicks that serves as an
antidote to chick TV, and it returns tonight - Sex In the City. By
BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
